I wasn&#39;t sure if it was audible since one can sort of hear irrational 
numbers with equal temperament. Perhaps the theory is that equal 
temperament sounds mostly like just intonation, and the only thing that 
we really want to hear is rational.  Everything else is just almost 
rational.

On 7/14/2013 9:38 AM, John H. Chalmers wrote:
&gt;
&gt; IIRC, John Chowning used the 9th root of pi in one of his pieces. Brink
&gt; McGoogy has used various combinations of e and pi (and phi, perhaps).
&gt; Brian McLaren probably has too. As Graham said, however,
&gt; one can&#39;t hear trancendentality.
&gt;
&gt; --john
